transcript.text: Hello, welcome to the own print shop.
In this video we will have a look at the Ship to Multiple Address feature enhancement.
In version 11.0, we have changed the flow of the feature and improved the interface, giving your customers a simplified screen to choose all the fields and proceed with their order placement.
Let's see how you can set up the Ship to Multiple Address feature and what will be the order flow.
In the Admin panel, navigate to the Store Configuration section and then click on the Site Settings.
In the search box, type Ship to and the associated settings will be displayed.
With the first setting, you can choose to enable the Ship to Multiple Address feature for the default store, private public stores, or both, or disable the feature.
The next setting is to choose how the Ship to Multiple Address feature will be displayed on the shopping cart page.
Here you can choose to display always or make it optional for the customers.
With the disable option, you can manage to enable this for one store and disable this for another.
The last setting is to define if you want to allow your customers to split the order product quantity or not by choosing yes or no.
Now let's go to the storefront and see how the order is placed via the Ship to Multiple Addresses flow.
In the shopping cart.
We have two products added and as we have selected optional in the second setting, we have a separate link for the Ship to Multiple address.
Let's click on the link and the next page.
Customers will now have the option to split the quantity selecting Ship Location and Shipping method from the single screen.
When the customer chooses to split the quantity, they will have the option to enter the quantity for multiple locations using the Add More Location link.
Once done, they can click on the Continue button.
The cart will update as per the customer's Joyce and the customer can now select the location and shipping method and then choose to continue for the checkout.
The rest of the checkout process remains as it is.
Once the order has been placed, the customer can see all the shipments created on the Order Details page.
Now in the Admin section under the View Order Details page, you will be able to see all the shipment details.
As you can see.
Also when you click on modify order, you will have the option to manage Ship to multiple addresses.
This page will allow the admin to manage the addresses on the customer's behalf.
These are all our new enhancements in the Ship to Multiple Addresses feature.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on on printshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
